<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880620-0033 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Geothermal Resources International </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GEO PPW </CO><IN> BON </IN><TEXT>   Geothermal Resources International Inc. said it missed a payment of about $532,000 due to a creditor June 1.    The San Mateo, Calif.-based geothermal energy concern said the creditor, Portland, Ore.-based PacifiCorp's PacifiCorp Credit Inc. unit, hasn't asserted a default on the $12.8 million in notes the payment relates to. The two companies are holding discussions, and Geothermal said it is seeking money for the payment from another source.    In composite trading on the American Stock Exchange, Geothermal closed Friday at $9.125, down 87.5 cents.    Geothermal also said it will pay a construction contractor $1.7 million in an arbitration award related to a contract dispute. </TEXT></DOC>